cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CYBER 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the impact of crowds on news engagement on a social platform. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also likely as the paper explores how users can alter the perception of news through changing the title of an article, which is related to social and behavioral aspects. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper studies features for predicting news popularity on a news aggregation platform. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper analyzes the impact of title changes on news popularity, which involves natural language processing. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) is less likely but still possible as the paper touches on the topic of platform manipulations of news and news popularity, which can have implications for cybersecurity.
